snippet: Al Nour, a party of ultraconservative Islamists, has emerged as an unexpected political kingmaker, shaping the interim government after the ouster of President Mohamed Morsi.
abstract: Al Nour, party of ultraconservative Islamists, has emerged as unexpected political kingmaker in Egypt, shaping interim government following military's ouster of pres Mohamed Morsi; group's presence during choreographed military takeover was meant to assure citizens that move was not attack on Islam; Al Nour tested its new-found leverage by blocking nomination of liberal Mohamed ElBaradei as interim Prime Min.
lead_paragraph: Al Nour, a party of ultraconservative Islamists, has emerged as an unexpected political kingmaker, shaping the interim government after the ouster of President Mohamed Morsi.
